<div class="newsbox odd">
<div class="newstitle label">Site Move </div>
<div class="newscontent"><br />First of all, sorry the site was in maintenance mode for so long. I was going to switch web hosts the first week of March but changed my mind and forgot to turn it off. March 29th-April 1st is now the new host-switching time. It should only take a few days.</div>
<div class="newsauthor">--Goku Girl on Mar 17, 2013 11:06 am ()</div>
<hr class="rule" />
</div>
<div class="newsbox even">
<div class="newstitle label">Submission rules update </div>
<div class="newscontent"><ol><li>I removed the link to the Front Page Express editor and added two new editors (BlueGriffon and KompoZer, which are both available to Windows, Mac, and Linux users.) If there are any that you think should be on the list (or removed from the list) please contact me.<br /><br /> </li><li>I added the following to the submission rules:<br /><br />&quot;All stories must be written in either prose style (like a novel) or  traditional screenplay style (like a play). Other styles are confusing  to readers.&quot;<br /><br /></li><li>I changed the rule about chapter length to exclude prologues and epilogues from the 500 word minimum. They must be at least 100 words, however.<br /></li></ol><p><br /><strong>Here are the highlights of the submission rules:</strong></p><ol><li>Stories must be in English.</li><li>Stories must be Dragon Ball-related unless you contact me first. If it&#39;s not fanfiction, it must go into the &quot;special content&quot; category. </li><li>Stories must be written in prose or screenplay style.<br /></li><li>Stories must have a disclaimer in either the story notes or the chapter notes of chapter 1.</li><li>Paragraphs must be double-spaced.</li><li>Stories must have good spelling, grammar, and punctuation. </li><li>Short stories must be at least 100 words. Chapters in stories must be at least 500 words (prologues/epilogues must be at least 100 words).</li><li>Author&#39;s notes/advertisements can&#39;t be separate chapters or longer than a chapter&#39;s actual story text. </li></ol></div>
<div class="newsauthor">--Goku Girl on Dec 10, 2011 03:01 pm ()</div>
